29 A child with a “functional developmental disability” means any person under the age of
30 eighteen (18) years or any person under the age of twenty-one (21) years who began to receive
31 services from the department prior to attaining eighteen (18) years of age and has continuously
32 received those services thereafter.
33 The term “functional developmental disability” includes autism spectrum disorders and
34 means a severe, chronic disability of a person that:
